snippet.textDisplay:
Several Christmas parades are held throughout the month of November in major Canadian cities, and Falun Dafa practitioners participated in four parades in the span of two days. Many spectators said they were moved by the music and learned about Falun Dafa.

On November 16, the Tian Guo Marching Band performed at the Newmarket parade at 11 a.m. They then hurried to Richmond Hill for a parade that started at 6 p.m. A team of waist drummers took part in the Christmas parade in Hamilton, which began at 4 p.m. The next day, the Tian Guo Marching Band performed at the Christmas parade in Milton.
